{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb35c1df-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s349"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"349"},"text":"§ 349.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rediscount for intermediate credit banks of obligations given for agricultural purposes; discount of notes made pursuant to section 1031","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any Federal reserve bank may, subject to regulations and limitations to be prescribed by the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, rediscount such notes, drafts, and bills mentioned in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s348"},"text":"section 348 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for any Federal intermediate credit bank, except that no Federal reserve bank shall rediscount for a Federal intermediate credit bank any such note or obligation which bears the indorsement of a nonmember State bank or trust company which is eligible for membership in the Federal reserve system in accordance with subchapter VIII of this chapter. Any Federal reserve bank may also, subject to regulations and limitations to be prescribed by the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, discount notes payable to and bearing the indorsement of any Federal intermediate credit bank covering loans or advances made by such bank pursuant to the provisions of section 1031 "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002040"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002040"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title which have maturities at the time of discount of not more than nine months, exclusive of days of grace, and which are secured by notes, drafts, or bills of exchange eligible for rediscount by Federal Reserve banks."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb35c1e0-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6/s13A"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6, § 13A","children":[],"tail":" (par.), formerly § 13a, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1923-03-04/ch252"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 252","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 404, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/1479"},"text":"42 Stat. 1479","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1932-05-19/ch191/s5"},"text":"May 19, 1932, ch. 191, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/47/160"},"text":"47 Stat. 160","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-23/ch614"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935, ch. 614","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 203(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/704"},"text":"49 Stat. 704","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 13A, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/242/tI/s142/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–242, title I, § 142(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/2281"},"text":"105 Stat. 2281","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb35c1e1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb35c1e2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddb35c1e3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subchapter VIII of this chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “section 9 of this Act”, meaning section 9 of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-12-23/ch6"},"text":"act Dec. 23, 1913, ch. 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/251"},"text":"38 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Reserve Act. Section 9 of the act is classified generally to subchapter VIII (§ 321 et seq.) of this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1031"},"text":"Section 1031 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/181/tV/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–181, title V, § 5","children":[],"tail":".26(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 1971","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/85/624"},"text":"85 Stat. 624","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2074"},"text":"section 2074 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb35c1e4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of second par. of section 13A, formerly section 13a, as added ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1923-03-04"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923","children":[],"tail":". Pars. 1, 3 to 5 of section 13A are set out as sections 348, 350 to 352 of this title, respectively."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb35c1e5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1932—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1932-05-19"},"text":"May 19, 1932","children":[],"tail":", inserted last sentence."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddb35c1e6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"iddb35c1e7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 203(a) of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1935","children":[],"tail":", changed name of Federal Reserve Board to Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
